This paper is about generating paraphrases, which is a natural language processing task. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a deep variational model, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses new training recipes and KL regularization techniques, which are related to optimization and regularization, respectively, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of paraphrases for machine reading comprehension and question answering, which are tasks related to natural language understanding, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of paraphrases in computer vision tasks, which could make cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
